>>> Starting Agent SpecificationRepairTask (2) OpenAIChatModel.GPT3_5_TURBO 
**Trial 1:**

**Fixed Specifications:** 
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors: set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches: set Class
}

/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}

/* The registered classes. */
sig Class {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups: Person -> Group
}

/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person {}

/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person {}

/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}

/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}

/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}

/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}

/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}

/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}

/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}

/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t: Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}

/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c: Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher
}

/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c: Class, s: Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}

/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c: Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}

/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t: Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}

/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}

/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all s: Student, c: Class, g: Group | some t: Teacher | t -> c in Teaches and some s.(c.Groups) and some t.(c.Groups) implies t in s.^~Tutors
}

/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s: Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}

/* IFF PERFECT ORACLE */
pred inv14_OK {
    all s: Person, c: Class, t: Person, g: Group | (c -> s -> g in Groups) and t -> c in Teaches implies t -> s in Tutors
}

assert inv14_Repaired {
    inv14[] iff inv14_OK[]
}

check inv14_Repaired expect 0
```

**Trial 1:**

**Fixed Specifications:** 
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors: set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches: set Class
}

/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}

/* The registered classes. */
sig Class {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups: Person -> Group
}

/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person {}

/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person {}

/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}

/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}

/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}

/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}

/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}

/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}

/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}

/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t: Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}

/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c: Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher
}

/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c: Class, s: Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}

/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c: Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}

/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t: Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}

/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}

/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all p: Person | some c: Class, g: Group | c->p->g in Groups implies p in Student and some t: Teacher | t->p in Tutors and t->c in Teaches
}

/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s: Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}

/* IFF Perfect Oracle */
pred inv14_OK {
    all s: Person, c: Class, t: Person, g: Group | (c -> s -> g in Groups) and t -> c in Teaches implies t -> s in Tutors
}

assert inv14_Repaired {
    inv14[] iff inv14_OK[]
}
```

**Trial 1:**

**Fixed Specifications:**
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person  {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors : set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches : set Class
}
/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}
/* The registered classes. */
sig Class  {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups : Person -> Group
}
/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person  {}
/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person  {}
/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}
/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}
/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}
/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}
/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}
/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t:Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}
/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c:Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher
}
/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c:Class, s:Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}
/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c : Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}
/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t : Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}
/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}
/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers
* assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all s:Student,c:Class,t:Teacher | s in c.Groups.Group
}
/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s : Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}
/*======== IFF PERFECT ORACLE ===============*/
pred inv1_OK {
    Person in Student
}
assert inv1_Repaired {
    inv1[] iff inv1_OK[]
}

**TOOL:**
```json
{
    "request": "run_alloy_analyzer",
    "specification": "/* The registered persons. */\nsig Person  {\n/* Each person tutors a set of persons. */\nTutors : set Person,\n/* Each person teaches a set of classes. */\nTeaches : set Class\n}\n/* The registered groups. */\nsig Group {}\n/* The registered classes. */\nsig Class  {\n/* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */\nGroups : Person -> Group\n}\n/* Some persons are teachers. */\nsig Teacher extends Person  {}\n/* Some persons are students. */\nsig Student extends Person  {}\n/* Every person is a student. */\npred inv1 {\nPerson in Student\n}\n/* There are no teachers. */\npred inv2 {\nno Teacher\n}\n/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */\npred inv3 {\nno Student & Teacher\n}\n/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */\npred inv4 {\nPerson in (Student + Teacher)\n}\n/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */\npred inv5 {\nsome Teacher.Teaches\n}\n/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */\npred inv6 {\nTeacher in Teaches.Class\n}\n/* Every class has teachers assigned. */\npred inv7 {\nClass in Teacher.Teaches\n}\n/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */\npred inv8 {\nall t:Teacher | lone t.Teaches\n}\n/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */\npred inv9 {\nall c:Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher\n}\n/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */\npred inv10 {\nall c:Class, s:Student | some s.(c.Groups)\n}\n/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */\npred inv11 {\nall c : Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c\n}\n/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */\npred inv12 {\nall t : Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups\n}\n/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */\npred inv13 {\nTutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in **Trial 1:**

**Fixed Specifications:** 
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person  {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors : set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches : set Class
}
/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}
/* The registered classes. */
sig Class  {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups : Person -> Group
}
/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person  {}
/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person  {}
/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}
/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}
/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}
/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}
/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}
/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t:Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}
/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c:Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher
}
/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c:Class, s:Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}
/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c : Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}
/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t : Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}
/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}
/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers
* assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all x : Person, y : Class, v : Teacher | (all z : Group | y->x->z in Groups) and v->y in Teaches implies v->x in Tutors
}
/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s : Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}
/*======== IFF PERFECT ORACLE ===============*/
pred inv1_OK {
    Person in Student
}
assert inv1_Repaired {
    inv1[] iff inv1_OK[]
}

**Fixed Specifications:** 
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors: set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches: set Class
}
/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}
/* The registered classes. */
sig Class {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups: Person -> Group
}
/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person {}
/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person {}
/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}
/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}
/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}
/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}
/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}
/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t: Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}
/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c: Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher
}
/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c: Class, s: Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}
/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c: Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}
/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t: Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}
/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}
/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers
* assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all s: Student, c: Class | some s.(c.Groups) implies some (Teacher <: Tutors).s
}
/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s: Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}
/*======== IFF PERFECT ORACLE ===============*/

**Fixed Specifications:**
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person  {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors : set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches : set Class
}
/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}
/* The registered classes. */
sig Class  {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups : Person -> Group
}
/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person  {}
/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person  {}
/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}
/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}
/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}
/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}
/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}
/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t:Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}
/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c:Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher
}
/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c:Class, s:Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}
/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c : Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}
/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t : Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}
/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}
/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers
* assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all s:Student,c:Class,g:Group|some t:Teacher | some c.Groups
}
/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s : Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}
/*======== IFF PERFECT ORACLE ===============*/
pred inv1_OK {
    Person in Student
}

**Trial 1:**

**Fixed Specifications:** 
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person  {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors : set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches : set Class
}
/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}
/* The registered classes. */
sig Class  {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups : Person -> Group
}
/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person  {}
/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person  {}
/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}
/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}
/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}
/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}
/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}
/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t:Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}
/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c:Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher
}
/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c:Class, s:Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}
/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c : Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}
/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t : Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}
/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}
/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers
* assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all x : Person, y : Class, v : Teacher | (some z : Group | y->x->z in Groups) and v->y in Teaches
}
/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s : Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}
/*======== IFF PERFECT ORACLE ===============*/
pred inv1_OK {
    Person in Student
}
assert inv1_Repaired {
    inv1[] iff inv1_OK[]
}

**Trial 1:**

**Fixed Specifications:** 
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors: set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches: set Class
}

/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}

/* The registered classes. */
sig Class {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups: Person -> Group
}

/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person {}

/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person {}

/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}

/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}

/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}

/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}

/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}

/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}

/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}

/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t: Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}

/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c: Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher
}

/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c: Class, s: Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}

/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c: Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}

/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t: Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}

/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}

/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all s: Student, c: Class | some s.(c.Groups)
}

/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s: Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}

/* IFF PERFECT ORACLE */
pred inv14_OK {
    all s: Person, c: Class, t: Person, g: Group | (c -> s -> g in Groups) and t -> c in Teaches implies t -> s in Tutors
}

assert inv14_Repaired {
    inv14[] iff inv14_OK[]
}

check inv14_Repaired expect 0
```

>>> Starting Agent SpecificationRepairTask (2) OpenAIChatModel.GPT3_5_TURBO 
**Trial 1:**

**Fixed Specifications:** 
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person  {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors : set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches : set Class
}
/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}
/* The registered classes. */
sig Class  {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups : Person -> Group
}
/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person  {}
/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person  {}
/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}
/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}
/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}
/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}
/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}
/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t:Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}
/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c:Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher
}
/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c:Class, s:Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}
/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c : Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}
/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t : Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}
/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}
/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers
* assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all s,t : Person, c : Class | some s.(c.Groups) and some (t.Teaches)
}
/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s : Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}
/*======== IFF PERFECT ORACLE ===============*/
pred inv1_OK {
    Person in Student
}

    "request": "run_alloy_analyzer",
    "specification": "/* The registered persons. */\nsig Person  {\n/* Each person tutors a set of persons. */\nTutors : set Person,\n/* Each person teaches a set of classes. */\nTeaches : set Class\n}\n/* The registered groups. */\nsig Group {}\n/* The registered classes. */\nsig Class  {\n/* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */\nGroups : Person -> Group\n}\n/* Some persons are teachers. */\nsig Teacher extends Person  {}\n/* Some persons are students. */\nsig Student extends Person  {}\n/* Every person is a student. */\npred inv1 {\nPerson in Student\n}\n/* There are no teachers. */\npred inv2 {\nno Teacher\n}\n/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */\npred inv3 {\nno Student & Teacher\n}\n/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */\npred inv4 {\nPerson in (Student + Teacher)\n}\n/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */\npred inv5 {\nsome Teacher.Teaches\n}\n/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */\npred inv6 {\nTeacher in Teaches.Class\n}\n/* Every class has teachers assigned. */\npred inv7 {\nClass in Teacher.Teaches\n}\n/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */\npred inv8 {\nall t:Teacher | lone t.Teaches\n}\n/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */\npred inv9 {\nall c:Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher\n}\n/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */\npred inv10 {\nall c:Class, s:Student **Trial 1:**

**Fixed Specifications:**
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person  {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors : set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches : set Class
}
/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}
/* The registered classes. */
sig Class  {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups : Person -> Group
}
/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person  {}
/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person  {}
/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}
/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}
/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}
/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}
/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}
/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t:Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}
/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c:Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher
}
/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c:Class, s:Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}
/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c : Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}
/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t : Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}
/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}
/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all c : Class, s : Student | some s.(c.Groups) & Teacher in (Teaches.c).Tutors
}
/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s : Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}
```

**Trial 1:**

**Fixed Specifications:**
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors: set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches: set Class
}

/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}

/* The registered classes. */
sig Class {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups: Person -> Group
}

/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person {}

/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person {}

/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}

/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}

/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}

/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}

/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}

/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}

/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}

/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t: Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}

/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c: Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher
}

/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c: Class, s: Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}

/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c: Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}

/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t: Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}

/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}

/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all s: Person, c: Class, t: Person, g: Group | (c -> s -> g in Groups) and t -> c in Teaches implies t -> s in Tutors
}

/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s: Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}

/* IFF Perfect Oracle */
pred inv14_OK {
    all s: Person, c: Class, t: Person, g: Group | (c -> s -> g in Groups) and t -> c in Teaches implies t -> s in Tutors
}

assert inv14_Repaired {
    inv14[] iff inv14_OK[]
}

check inv14_Repaired expect 0
```

**Trial 1:**

**Fixed Specifications:** 
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person  {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors : set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches : set Class
}
/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}
/* The registered classes. */
sig Class  {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups : Person -> Group
}
/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person  {}
/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person  {}
/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}
/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}
/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}
/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}
/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}
/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t:Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}
/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c:Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher
}
/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c:Class, s:Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}
/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c : Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}
/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t : Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}
/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}
/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers
* assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all c : Class | (c . (Groups . Group)) in (Teaches . c . Tutors) & Student
}
/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s : Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}
```

**Request:**

>>> Starting Agent SpecificationRepairTask (2) OpenAIChatModel.GPT3_5_TURBO 
**Trial 1:**

**Fixed Specifications:**
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person  {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors : set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches : set Class
}
/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}
/* The registered classes. */
sig Class  {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups : Person -> Group
}
/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person  {}
/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person  {}
/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}
/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}
/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}
/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}
/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}
/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t:Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}
/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c:Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher
}
/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c:Class, s:Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}
/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c : Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}
/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t : Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}
/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}
/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all c:Class , t:Teacher, s:Student, g:Group|(c->s->g in Groups and t->c in Teaches) implies t->c in Tutors
}
/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s : Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}
```

no Teacher } /* No person is both a student and a teacher. */ pred inv3 { no Student & Teacher } /* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */ pred inv4 { Person in (Student + Teacher) } /* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */ pred inv5 { some Teacher.Teaches } /* Every teacher has classes assigned. */ pred inv6 { Teacher in Teaches.Class } /* Every class has teachers assigned. */ pred inv7 { Class in Teacher.Teaches } /* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */ pred inv8 { all t:Teacher | lone t.Teaches } /* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */ pred inv9 { all c:Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher } /* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */ pred inv10 { all c:Class, s:Student | some s.(c.Groups) } /* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */ pred inv11 { all c : Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c } /* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */ pred inv12 { all t : Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups } /* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */ pred inv13 { Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student } /* Every student in a class is at least tutored by >>> Starting Agent SpecificationRepairTask (2) OpenAIChatModel.GPT3_5_TURBO 
**Trial 1:**

**Fixed Specifications:**
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person  {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors : set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches : set Class
}
/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}
/* The registered classes. */
sig Class  {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups : Person -> Group
}
/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person  {}
/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person  {}
/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}
/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}
/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}
/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}
/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}
/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t:Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}
/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c:Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher
}
/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c:Class, s:Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}
/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c : Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}
/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t : Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}
/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}
/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers
* assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all c : Class | (c . (Groups . Group)) & Student = ((Teaches . c) . Tutors)
}
/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s : Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}
```

**Fixed Specifications:** 
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors: set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches: set Class
}
/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}
/* The registered classes. */
sig Class {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups: Person -> Group
}
/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person {}
/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person {}
/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}
/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}
/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}
/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}
/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}
/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t: Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}
/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c: Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher
}
/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c: Class, s: Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}
/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c: Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}
/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t: Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}
/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}
/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all s, t: Person, c: Class | (some g: Group | c->s->g in Groups) and t->s in Tutors implies t->c in Teaches
}
/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s: Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}
/*======== IFF PERFECT ORACLE ===============*/
pred inv1_OK {
    Person in Student
}
assert inv1_Repaired {

**Trial 1:**

**Fixed Specifications:** 
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors: set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches: set Class
}
/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}
/* The registered classes. */
sig Class {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups: Person -> Group
}
/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person {}
/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person {}
/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}
/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}
/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}
/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}
/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}
/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t: Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}
/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c: Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher
}
/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c: Class, s: Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}
/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c: Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}
/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t: Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}
/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}
/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all s: Student, c: Class | s in c.Groups.Group implies some t: Teacher | t -> c in Teaches
}
/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s: Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}
/*======== IFF PERFECT ORACLE ===============*/
pred inv1_OK {
    Person in Student
}
assert inv1_Repaired {
    inv1[] iff inv1_OK[]
}
---------
pred inv2_OK {
    no Teacher
}
assert inv2_Repaired {
    inv2[] iff inv2_OK[]
}
--------
pred inv3_OK {

**Trial 1:**

**Fixed Specifications:**
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors: set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches: set Class
}

/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}

/* The registered classes. */
sig Class {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups: Person -> Group
}

/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person {}

/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person {}

/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}

/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}

/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}

/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}

/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}

/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}

/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}

/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t: Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}

/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c: Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher
}

/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c: Class, s: Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}

/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c: Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}

/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t: Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}

/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}

/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all s: Student, c: Class | some t: Teacher | t->s in Tutors implies t->c in Teaches
}

/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s: Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}

/* IFF PERFECT ORACLE */
pred inv14_OK {
    all s: Person, c: Class, t: Person, g: Group | (c -> s -> g in Groups) and t -> c in Teaches implies t -> s in Tutors
}

assert inv14_Repaired {
    inv14[] iff inv14_OK[]
}

check inv14_Repaired expect 0
```

sig Teacher extends Person {}

sig Student extends Person {}

pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}

pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}

pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}

pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}

pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}

pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}

pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}

pred inv8 {
    all t: Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}

pred inv9 {
    all c: Class | lone c.Groups & Teacher
}

pred inv10 {
    all c: Class, s: Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}

pred inv11 {
    all c: Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}

pred inv12 {
    all t: Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}

pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}

pred inv14 {
    all s: Student | some t: Teacher, c: Class | t->s in Tutors and t->c in Teaches
}

pred inv15 {
    all s: Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}

pred inv14_OK {
    all s: Person, c: Class, t: Person, g: Group | (c -> s -> g in Groups) and t -> c in Teaches implies t -> s in Tutors
}

assert inv14_Repaired {
    inv14[] iff inv14_OK[]
}

check inv14_Repaired expect 0
```

{
    "request": "run_alloy_analyzer",
    "specification": "/* The registered persons. */ sig Person  { /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */ Tutors : set Person, /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */ Teaches : set Class } /* The registered groups. */ sig Group {} /* The registered classes. */ sig Class  { /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */ Groups : Person -> Group } /* Some persons are teachers. */ sig Teacher extends Person  {} /* Some persons are students. */ sig Student extends Person  {} /* Every person is a student. */ pred inv1 { Person in Student } /* There are no teachers. */ pred inv2 { no Teacher } /* No person is both a student and a teacher. */ pred inv3 { no Student & Teacher } /* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */ pred inv4 { Person in (Student + Teacher) } /* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */ pred inv5 { some Teacher.Teaches } /* Every teacher has classes assigned. */ pred inv6 { Teacher in Teaches.Class } /* Every class has teachers assigned. */ pred inv7 { Class in Teacher.Teaches } /* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */ pred inv8 { all t:Teacher | lone t.Teaches } /* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */ pred inv9 { all c:Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher } /* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */ pred inv10 { all c:Class, s:Student | some s.(c.Groups) } /* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */ pred inv11 { all c : Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c } /* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */ pred inv12 { all t : Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups } /* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */ pred inv13 { Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student } /* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers * assigned to that class. */ pred inv14 { all p : Student | some c : Class, g : Group | c->p->g in Groups implies some t : Teacher | t->p in Tutors and t->c in Teaches } /* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */ pred inv15 { all s : Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s }"
}

Class | lone t: Teacher | t in c.Teaches\n}\n/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */\npred inv10 {\n    all c: Class, s: Student | some g: Group | g in c.Groups[s]\n}\n/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */\npred inv11 {\n    all c: Class | (some g: Group | g in c.Groups) implies some t: Teacher | t in c.Teaches\n}\n/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */\npred inv12 {\n    all t: Teacher | some g: Group | g in (t.Teaches).Groups\n}\n/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */\npred inv13 {\n    all p: Person | p in Teacher iff ```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors: set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches: set Class
}
/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}
/* The registered classes. */
sig Class {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups: Person -> Group
}
/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person {}
/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person {}
/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}
/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}
/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}
/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}
/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}
/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t: Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}
/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c: Class | lone c.Teaches & Teacher
}
/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c: Class, s: Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}
/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c: Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}
/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t: Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}
/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}
/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers
* assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all s: Person, c: Class | some s.(Teacher<:Tutors) implies some c.(Teacher<:Teaches)
}
/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s: Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}
/*======== IFF PERFECT ORACLE ===============*/
pred inv1_OK {
    Person in Student
}
assert inv1_Repaired {

**Trial 1:**

**Fixed Specifications**:

```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person  {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors : set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches : set Class
}
/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}
/* The registered classes. */
sig Class  {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups : Person -> Group
}
/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person  {}
/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person  {}
/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}
/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}
/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}
/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}
/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}
/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t:Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}
/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c:Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher
}
/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c:Class, s:Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}
/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c : Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}
/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t : Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}
/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}
/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers
* assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all t : Teacher, c : Class | some Student.(c.Groups) and some (t<:Teaches).c implies some (t<:Tutors).Student
}
/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s : Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}
/*======== IFF PERFECT ORACLE ===============*/
pred inv1_OK {
    Person in Student
}

**Trial 1:**

**Fixed Specifications:** 
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors: set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches: set Class
}
/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}
/* The registered classes. */
sig Class {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups: Person -> Group
}
/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person {}
/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person {}
/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}
/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}
/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}
/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}
/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}
/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t: Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}
/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c: Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher
}
/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c: Class, s: Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}
/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c: Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}
/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t: Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}
/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}
/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers
* assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all p: Person | some c: Class, g: Group | c->p->g in Groups implies some q: Person | q->p in Tutors and q->c in Teaches
}
/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s: Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}
/*======== IFF PERFECT ORACLE ===============*/
pred inv1_OK {
    Person in Student
}

**Trial 1:**

**Fixed Specifications:**
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors: set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches: set Class
}

/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}

/* The registered classes. */
sig Class {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups: Person -> Group
}

/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person {}

/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person {}

/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}

/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}

/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}

/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}

/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}

/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}

/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}

/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t: Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}

/* No class has more than one teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c: Class | lone c.Teaches & Teacher
}

/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c: Class, s: Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}

/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c: Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}

/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t: Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}

/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}

/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all p: Person | some c: Class, g: Group | c->p->g in Groups implies some q: Person | q->c in Teaches and q->p in Tutors
}

/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s: Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}

/* IFF Perfect Oracle */
pred inv14_OK {
    all s: Person, c: Class, t: Person, g: Group | (c -> s -> g in Groups) and t -> c in Teaches implies t -> s in Tutors
}

assert inv14_Repaired {
    inv14[] iff inv14_OK[]
}

check inv14_Repaired expect 0
```

Group\n}\n\n/* Some persons are teachers. */\nsig Teacher extends Person {}\n\n/* Some persons are students. */\nsig Student extends Person {}\n\n/* Every person is a student. */\npred inv1 {\n    Person in Student\n}\n\n/* There are no teachers. */\npred inv2 {\n    no Teacher\n}\n\n/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */\npred inv3 {\n    no Student & Teacher\n}\n\n/* No person is **Trial 1:**

**Fixed Specifications:** 
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors: set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches: set Class
}

/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}

/* The registered classes. */
sig Class {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups: Person -> Group
}

/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person {}

/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person {}

/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}

/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}

/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}

/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}

/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}

/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}

/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}

/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t: Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}

/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c: Class | lone c.Teaches & Teacher
}

/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c: Class, s: Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}

/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c: Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}

/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t: Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}

/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}

/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all s: Student | some t: Teacher, c: Class, g: Group | t->c in Teaches implies t->s in Tutors
}

/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s: Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}

/* IFF Perfect Oracle */
pred inv14_OK {
    all s: Person, c: Class, t: Person, g: Group | (c -> s -> g in Groups) and t -> c in Teaches implies t -> s in Tutors
}

assert inv14_Repaired {
    inv14[] iff inv14_OK[]
}

check inv14_Repaired expect 0
```

**Trial 1:**

**Fixed Specifications:** 
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person  {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors : set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches : set Class
}
/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}
/* The registered classes. */
sig Class  {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups : Person -> Group
}
/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person  {}
/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person  {}
/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}
/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}
/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}
/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}
/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}
/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t:Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}
/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c:Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher
}
/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c:Class, s:Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}
/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c : Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}
/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t : Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}
/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}
/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers
* assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all s : Person, c : Class | some c -> s <: Groups implies (Teaches . c) -> s in Tutors
}
/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s : Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}
/*======== IFF PERFECT ORACLE ===============*/
pred inv14_OK {
    all s : Person, c : Class, t : Person, g : Group | (c -> s -> g in Groups) and t -> c in Teaches implies t -> s in Tutors
}
assert inv14_Repaired {
    inv14[] iff inv14_OK[]
}
```

**Trial 1:**

**Fixed Specifications:** 
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person  {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors : set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches : set Class
}
/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}
/* The registered classes. */
sig Class  {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups : Person -> Group
}
/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person  {}
/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person  {}
/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}
/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}
/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}
/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}
/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}
/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t:Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}
/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c:Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher
}
/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c:Class, s:Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}
/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c : Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}
/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t : Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}
/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}
/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers
* assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all s:Student, c:Class | some t:Teacher, g:Group | t->s in Tutors and c->s->g in Groups and c->t->g in Groups
}
/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s : Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}
/*======== IFF PERFECT ORACLE ===============*/
pred inv1_OK {
    Person in Student
}
assert inv1_Repaired {
    inv1[] iff inv1_OK[]
}
---------
pred inv2_OK {
    no Teacher

**Trial 1:**

**Fixed Specifications:** 
```alloy
sig Person {
    Tutors: set Person,
    Teaches: set Class
}

sig Group {}

sig Class {
    Groups: Person lone -> Group
}

sig Teacher extends Person {}

sig Student extends Person {}

pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}

pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}

pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}

pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}

pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}

pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}

pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}

pred inv8 {
    all t: Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}

pred inv9 {
    all c: Class | lone c.Groups & Teacher
}

pred inv10 {
    all c: Class, s: Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}

pred inv11 {
    all c: Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}

pred inv12 {
    all t: Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}

pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}

pred inv14 {
    all s: Student, c: Class | some t: Teacher | s in c.Groups.Group and t in c.Groups.Group implies t in s.^(~Tutors)
}

pred inv15 {
    all s: Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}

pred inv14_OK {
    all s: Person, c: Class, t: Person, g: Group | (c -> s -> g in Groups) and t -> c in Teaches implies t -> s in Tutors
}

assert inv14_Repaired {
    inv14[] iff inv14_OK[]
}

check inv14_Repaired expect 0
```

**Trial 1:**

**Fixed Specifications:** 
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors: set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches: set Class
}

/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}

/* The registered classes. */
sig Class {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups: Person -> Group
}

/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person {}

/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person {}

/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}

/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}

/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}

/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}

/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}

/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}

/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}

/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t: Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}

/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c: Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher
}

/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c: Class, s: Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}

/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c: Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}

/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t: Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}

/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}

/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all s: Student, c: Class | some c.(Teacher<:Teaches) implies some s.(Teacher<:Tutors)
}

/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s: Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}

/* IFF PERFECT ORACLE */
pred inv14_OK {
    all s: Person, c: Class, t: Person, g: Group | (c -> s -> g in Groups) and t -> c in Teaches implies t -> s in Tutors
}

assert inv14_Repaired {
    inv14[] iff inv14_OK[]
}
```

**Trial 1:**

**Fixed Specifications:** 
```alloy
/* The registered persons. */
sig Person  {
    /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */
    Tutors : set Person,
    /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */
    Teaches : set Class
}
/* The registered groups. */
sig Group {}
/* The registered classes. */
sig Class  {
    /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */
    Groups : Person -> Group
}
/* Some persons are teachers. */
sig Teacher extends Person  {}
/* Some persons are students. */
sig Student extends Person  {}
/* Every person is a student. */
pred inv1 {
    Person in Student
}
/* There are no teachers. */
pred inv2 {
    no Teacher
}
/* No person is both a student and a teacher. */
pred inv3 {
    no Student & Teacher
}
/* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */
pred inv4 {
    Person in (Student + Teacher)
}
/* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */
pred inv5 {
    some Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Every teacher has classes assigned. */
pred inv6 {
    Teacher in Teaches.Class
}
/* Every class has teachers assigned. */
pred inv7 {
    Class in Teacher.Teaches
}
/* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */
pred inv8 {
    all t:Teacher | lone t.Teaches
}
/* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */
pred inv9 {
    all c:Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher
}
/* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */
pred inv10 {
    all c:Class, s:Student | some s.(c.Groups)
}
/* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */
pred inv11 {
    all c : Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c
}
/* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */
pred inv12 {
    all t : Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups
}
/* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */
pred inv13 {
    Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student
}
/* Every student in a class is at least tutored by all the teachers
* assigned to that class. */
pred inv14 {
    all s : Student, c : Class | some t : Teacher, g : Group | t->c in Teaches implies t->s in Tutors and c->s->g in Groups
}
/* The tutoring chain of every person eventually reaches a Teacher. */
pred inv15 {
    all s : Person | some Teacher & ^Tutors.s
}
/*======== IFF PERFECT ORACLE ===============*/
pred inv14_OK {
    all s : Person, c : Class, t : Person, g : Group | (c -> s -> g in Groups) and t -> c in Teaches implies t -> s in Tutors
}
assert inv14_Repaired {
    inv14[] iff inv14_OK[]
}
```

{
    "request": "run_alloy_analyzer",
    "specification": "/* The registered persons. */ sig Person { /* Each person tutors a set of persons. */ Tutors : set Person, /* Each person teaches a set of classes. */ Teaches : set Class } /* The registered groups. */ sig Group {} /* The registered classes. */ sig Class { /* Each class has a set of persons assigned to a group. */ Groups : Person -> Group } /* Some persons are teachers. */ sig Teacher extends Person {} /* Some persons are students. */ sig Student extends Person {} /* Every person is a student. */ pred inv1 { Person in Student } /* There are no teachers. */ pred inv2 { no Teacher } /* No person is both a student and a teacher. */ pred inv3 { no Student & Teacher } /* No person is neither a student nor a teacher. */ pred inv4 { Person in (Student + Teacher) } /* There are some classes assigned to teachers. */ pred inv5 { some Teacher.Teaches } /* Every teacher has classes assigned. */ pred inv6 { Teacher in Teaches.Class } /* Every class has teachers assigned. */ pred inv7 { Class in Teacher.Teaches } /* Teachers are assigned at most one class. */ pred inv8 { all t:Teacher | lone t.Teaches } /* No class has more than a teacher assigned. */ pred inv9 { all c:Class | lone Teaches.c & Teacher } /* For every class, every student has a group assigned. */ pred inv10 { all c:Class, s:Student | some s.(c.Groups) } /* A class only has groups if it has a teacher assigned. */ pred inv11 { all c : Class | (some c.Groups) implies some Teacher & Teaches.c } /* Each teacher is responsible for some groups. */ pred inv12 { all t : Teacher | some (t.Teaches).Groups } /* Only teachers tutor, and only students are tutored. */ pred inv13 { Tutors.Person in Teacher and Person.Tutors in Student } /* Every student in a class is at least tutored by
